The article discusses a Presidential Memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on September 28, 2018. The memorandum pertains to the Child Soldiers Prevention Act of 2008 (CSPA) and determines that it is in the national interest of the United States to waive the prohibition in section 404(a) of the CSPA for Iraq, Mali, Niger, and Nigeria. The memorandum also waives the prohibition for Somalia, South Sudan, and Yemen to allow for various forms of assistance and support, including International Military Education and Training, Peacekeeping Operations assistance, and support provided under 10 U.S.C. 333. The determination is to be submitted to Congress along with a Memorandum of Justification and published in the Federal Register.